swAuthCtrl.name: swAuthCtrl
swAuthCtrl.description: The Structure of Common Management Information for the security functions of the devices.

PortList.name: PortList
PortList.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the bridge is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'.

VlanId.name: VlanId
VlanId.description: A 12-bit VLAN ID used in the VLAN Tag header.

authProtocol.name: authProtocol
authProtocol.description: The authentication method used to authenticate users.

swAuthMode.name: swAuthMode
swAuthMode.description: This object indicates the authentication mode of the device.

swAuthorizationState.name: swAuthorizationState
swAuthorizationState.description: This object indicates the authorization status.

swAuthFailOver.name: swAuthFailOver
swAuthFailOver.description: This object indicates the fail over status.

swRadiusDeadTime.name: swRadiusDeadTime
swRadiusDeadTime.description: Specifies the number of minutes when a RADIUS server that is not responding to authentication requests, is considered unavailable and will no longer accept further requests for RADIUS authentication.

swRadiusTimeout.name: swRadiusTimeout
swRadiusTimeout.description: Specifies the number of seconds the NAS will wait for a reply to a RADIUS request before retransmitting the request.

swRadiusRetransmitAttempts.name: swRadiusRetransmitAttempts
swRadiusRetransmitAttempts.description: Specifies the number of times the NAS transmits each RADIUS request to the server before giving up.

swRadiusServerEntry.name: swRadiusServerEntry
swRadiusServerEntry.description: The entries of the RADIUS server table

swRadiusServerIndex.name: swRadiusServerIndex
swRadiusServerIndex.description: The index of the RADIUS server

swRadiusServerIpAddr.name: swRadiusServerIpAddr
swRadiusServerIpAddr.description: The IP address of the RADIUS server

swRadiusServerKey.name: swRadiusServerKey
swRadiusServerKey.description: The key of the RADIUS server

swRadiusAuthPortNumber.name: swRadiusAuthPortNumber
swRadiusAuthPortNumber.description: The UDP destination port number used for authentication requests to this server.

swRadiusAcctPortNumber.name: swRadiusAcctPortNumber
swRadiusAcctPortNumber.description: The UDP destination port number used for accounting requests to this server

swRadiusServerStatus.name: swRadiusServerStatus
swRadiusServerStatus.description: The status of the RADIUS server

swRadiusServerTimeout.name: swRadiusServerTimeout
swRadiusServerTimeout.description: Specifies the number of seconds the NAS will wait for a reply to a RADIUS request before retransmitting the request.

swRadiusServerRetransmit.name: swRadiusServerRetransmit
swRadiusServerRetransmit.description: Specifies the number of times the NAS transmits RADIUS requests to the server before giving up.

swRadiusServerAddrType.name: swRadiusServerAddrType
swRadiusServerAddrType.description: The type of RADIUS Server address as specified by object 'swRadiusServerAddr'.

swRadiusServerAddr.name: swRadiusServerAddr
swRadiusServerAddr.description: The address of the RADIUS Server.

swRadiusVrfName.name: swRadiusVrfName
swRadiusVrfName.description: This object is used to add or remove the VRF for 802.1X RADIUS

swRadiusAuthClientIdentifier.name: swRadiusAuthClientIdentifier
swRadiusAuthClientIdentifier.description: NAS Identifier. It was made obsolete by RFC 2618 and RFC 2620.

swRadiusAuthClientInvalidServerAddresses.name: swRadiusAuthClientInvalidServerAddresses
swRadiusAuthClientInvalidServerAddresses.description: Statistics infomation - The number of RADIUS Access-Response packets received from unknown addresses. It was made obsolete by RFC 2618 and RFC 2620.

swRadiusAuthServerTable.name: swRadiusAuthServerTable
swRadiusAuthServerTable.description: The authenticate table for the RADIUS server.

swRadiusAuthServerEntry.name: swRadiusAuthServerEntry
swRadiusAuthServerEntry.description: A list of RADIUS authentication servers. It was made obsolete by RFC 2618 and RFC 2620.

swRadiusAuthServerIndex.name: swRadiusAuthServerIndex
swRadiusAuthServerIndex.description: The RADIUS Server Index. It was made obsolete by RFC 2618 and RFC 2620.

swRadiusAuthServerAddress.name: swRadiusAuthServerAddress
swRadiusAuthServerAddress.description: The RADIUS authentication server address. It was made obsolete by RFC 2618 and RFC 2620.

swRadiusAuthClientServerPortNumber.name: swRadiusAuthClientServerPortNumber
swRadiusAuthClientServerPortNumber.description: The UDP socket port numbers. It was made obsolete by RFC 2618 and RFC 2620.

swRadiusAuthClientRoundTripTime.name: swRadiusAuthClientRoundTripTime
swRadiusAuthClientRoundTripTime.description: The round trip time counter from the RADIUS Authentication Client. It was made obsolete by RFC 2618 and RFC 2620.

swRadiusAuthClientAccessRequests.name: swRadiusAuthClientAccessRequests
swRadiusAuthClientAccessRequests.description: The number of access requests from a RADIUS Authentication Client. It was made obsolete by RFC 2618 and RFC 2620.

swRadiusAuthClientAccessRetransmissions.name: swRadiusAuthClientAccessRetransmissions
swRadiusAuthClientAccessRetransmissions.description: The number of retransmissions sent from the RADIUS Authentication Client. It was made obsolete by RFC 2618 and RFC 2620.

swRadiusAuthClientAccessAccepts.name: swRadiusAuthClientAccessAccepts
swRadiusAuthClientAccessAccepts.description: The number of authentication access attempts from the RADIUS Authentication Client. It was made obsolete by RFC 2618 and RFC 2620.

swRadiusAuthClientAccessRejects.name: swRadiusAuthClientAccessRejects
swRadiusAuthClientAccessRejects.description: The counter stating the Client Access Authentication rejections. It was made obsolete by RFC 2618 and RFC 2620.

swRadiusAuthClientAccessChallenges.name: swRadiusAuthClientAccessChallenges
swRadiusAuthClientAccessChallenges.description: The counter stating the number of Access challenges from RADIUS authentication attempts. It was made obsolete by RFC 2618 and RFC 2620.

swRadiusAuthClientMalformedAccessRespons.name: swRadiusAuthClientMalformedAccessResponses
swRadiusAuthClientMalformedAccessRespons.description: The counter for malformed access responses from RADIUS Authentication Clients. It was made obsolete by RFC 2618 and RFC 2620.

swRadiusAuthClientBadAuthenticators.name: swRadiusAuthClientBadAuthenticators
swRadiusAuthClientBadAuthenticators.description: The counter of bad authenticators from the RADIUS Authentication Client. It was made obsolete by RFC 2618 and RFC 2620.

swRadiusAuthClientPendingRequests.name: swRadiusAuthClientPendingRequests
swRadiusAuthClientPendingRequests.description: The counter of pending requests from the RADIUS Authentication Client. It was made obsolete by RFC 2618 and RFC 2620.

swRadiusAuthClientTimeouts.name: swRadiusAuthClientTimeouts
swRadiusAuthClientTimeouts.description: The counter of timeouts from a RADIUS Authentication Client. It was made obsolete by RFC 2618 and RFC 2620.

swRadiusAuthClientUnknownTypes.name: swRadiusAuthClientUnknownTypes
swRadiusAuthClientUnknownTypes.description: The counter for unknown types from a RADIUS Authentication Client. It was made obsolete by RFC 2618 and RFC 2620.

swRadiusAuthClientPacketsDropped.name: swRadiusAuthClientPacketsDropped
swRadiusAuthClientPacketsDropped.description: The counter of dropped packets from a RADIUS Authentication Client. It was made obsolete by RFC 2618 and RFC 2620.

swRadiusAcctUpdateInterval.name: swRadiusAcctUpdateInterval
swRadiusAcctUpdateInterval.description: Time interval after which this RADIUS record should be updated and sent to an accounting server.

swRadiusAcctSuppressNullUserName.name: swRadiusAcctSuppressNullUserName
swRadiusAcctSuppressNullUserName.description: Indicates whether or not accounting records will be generated for users with null names.

swMacAuthStateTable.description: A table that contains the status objects for the Authenticator PAE associated with each virtual port (MAC address). An entry appears in this table for each virtual port that may authenticate access to itself.

swMacAuthStateEntry.description: The information for an Authenticator PAE.

swPaePortNumber.name: swPaePortNumber
swPaePortNumber.description: The PAE Port number associated with this Port.

swAuthPaeState.name: swAuthPaeState

swAuthAuthControlledPortStatus.name: swAuthAuthControlledPortStatus

swMacAuthStatsTable.description: A table that contains the statistics objects for the Authenticator PAE associated with each MAC address. An entry appears in this table for each MAC address that may authenticate access to itself.

swAuthEapolFramesRx.description: The number of valid EAPOL frames of any type that have been received by this Authenticator.

swAuthEapolFramesTx.name: swAuthEapolFramesTx
swAuthEapolFramesTx.description: The number of EAPOL frames of any type that have been transmitted by this Authenticator.

swAuthEapolStartFramesRx.name: swAuthEapolStartFramesRx
swAuthEapolStartFramesRx.description: The number of EAPOL Start frames that have been received by this Authenticator.

swAuthEapolLogoffFramesRx.name: swAuthEapolLogoffFramesRx
swAuthEapolLogoffFramesRx.description: The number of EAPOL logoff frames that have been received by this Authenticator.

swAuthEapolRespIdFramesRx.name: swAuthEapolRespIdFramesRx
swAuthEapolRespIdFramesRx.description: The number of EAP Resp/Id frames that have been received by this Authenticator.

swAuthEapolRespFramesRx.name: swAuthEapolRespFramesRx
swAuthEapolRespFramesRx.description: The number of valid EAP Response frames, other than Resp/Id frames, that have been received by this Authenticator.

swAuthEapolReqIdFramesTx.name: swAuthEapolReqIdFramesTx
swAuthEapolReqIdFramesTx.description: The number of EAP Req/Id frames that have been transmitted by this Authenticator.

swAuthEapolReqFramesTx.name: swAuthEapolReqFramesTx
swAuthEapolReqFramesTx.description: The number of EAP Request frames, other than Rq/Id frames, that have been transmitted by this Authenticator.

swAuthInvalidEapolFramesRx.name: swAuthInvalidEapolFramesRx
swAuthInvalidEapolFramesRx.description: The number of EAPOL frames that have been received by this Authenticator for which the frame type is not recognized.

swAuthEapLengthErrorFramesRx.name: swAuthEapLengthErrorFramesRx
swAuthEapLengthErrorFramesRx.description: The number of EAPOL frames that have been received by this Authenticator for which the Packet Body Length field is invalid.

swAuthLastEapolFrameVersion.name: swAuthLastEapolFrameVersion
swAuthLastEapolFrameVersion.description: The protocol version number carried in the most recently received EAPOL frame.

swAuthLastEapolFrameSource.name: swAuthLastEapolFrameSource
swAuthLastEapolFrameSource.description: The source MAC address carried in the most recently received EAPOL frame.

swMacAuthDiagTable.name: swMacAuthDiagTable
swMacAuthDiagTable.description: A table that contains the diagnostics objects for the Authenticator PAE associated with each MAC address. An entry appears in this table for each MAC address that may authenticate access to itself.

swMacAuthDiagEntry.name: swMacAuthDiagEntry
swMacAuthDiagEntry.description: The diagnostics information for an Authenticator PAE.

swAuthEntersConnecting.name: swAuthEntersConnecting
swAuthEntersConnecting.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions to a CONNECTING state from any other state.

swAuthEapLogoffsWhileConnecting.name: swAuthEapLogoffsWhileConnecting
swAuthEapLogoffsWhileConnecting.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from CONNECTING to DISCONNECTED as a result of receiving an EAPOL-Logoff message.

swAuthEntersAuthenticating.name: swAuthEntersAuthenticating
swAuthEntersAuthenticating.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from CONNECTING to AUTHENTICATING, as a result of an EAP-Response/Identity message being received from the Supplicant.

swAuthAuthSuccessWhileAuthenticating.name: swAuthAuthSuccessWhileAuthenticating
swAuthAuthSuccessWhileAuthenticating.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATING to AUTHENTICATED, as a result of the Backend Authentication state machine, indicating successful authentication of the Supplicant (authSuccess = TRUE).

swAuthAuthTimeoutsWhileAuthenticating.name: swAuthAuthTimeoutsWhileAuthenticating
swAuthAuthTimeoutsWhileAuthenticating.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATING to ABORTING, as a result of the Backend Authentication state machine indicating authentication timeout (authTimeout = TRUE).

swAuthAuthFailWhileAuthenticating.name: swAuthAuthFailWhileAuthenticating
swAuthAuthFailWhileAuthenticating.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATING to HELD, as a result of the Backend Authentication state machine indicating authentication failure (authFail = TRUE).

swAuthAuthReauthsWhileAuthenticating.name: swAuthAuthReauthsWhileAuthenticating
swAuthAuthReauthsWhileAuthenticating.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATING to ABORTING, as a result of a reauthentication request (reAuthenticate = TRUE).

swAuthAuthEapStartsWhileAuthenticating.name: swAuthAuthEapStartsWhileAuthenticating
swAuthAuthEapStartsWhileAuthenticating.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATING to ABORTING, as a result of an EAPOL-Start message being received from the Supplicant.

swAuthAuthEapLogoffWhileAuthenticating.name: swAuthAuthEapLogoffWhileAuthenticating
swAuthAuthEapLogoffWhileAuthenticating.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATING to ABORTING, as a result of an EAPOL-Logoff message being received from the Supplicant.

swAuthAuthReauthsWhileAuthenticated.name: swAuthAuthReauthsWhileAuthenticated
swAuthAuthReauthsWhileAuthenticated.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATED to CONNECTING, as a result of a reauthentication request (reAuthenticate = TRUE).

swAuthAuthEapStartsWhileAuthenticated.name: swAuthAuthEapStartsWhileAuthenticated
swAuthAuthEapStartsWhileAuthenticated.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATED to CONNECTING, as a result of an EAPOL-Start message received from the Supplicant.

swAuthAuthEapLogoffWhileAuthenticated.name: swAuthAuthEapLogoffWhileAuthenticated
swAuthAuthEapLogoffWhileAuthenticated.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATED to DISCONNECTED, as a result of an EAPOL-Logoff message received from the Supplicant.

swAuthBackendResponses.name: swAuthBackendResponses
swAuthBackendResponses.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine sends an initial Access-Request packet to the Authentication server (i.e., executes sendRespToServer on entry to the RESPONSE state). Indicates that the Authenticator attempted communication with the Authentication Server.

swAuthBackendAccessChallenges.name: swAuthBackendAccessChallenges
swAuthBackendAccessChallenges.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine receives an initial Access-Challenge packet from the Authentication server (i.e., aReq becomes TRUE, causing exit from the RESPONSE state). Indicates that the Authentication Server has communication with the Authenticator.

swAuthBackendOtherRequestsToSupplicant.name: swAuthBackendOtherRequestsToSupplicant
swAuthBackendOtherRequestsToSupplicant.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine sends an EAP-Request packet (other than an Identity, Notification, Failure or Success message) to the Supplicant (i.e., executes txReq on entry to the REQUEST state). Indicates that the Authenticator chose an EAP-method.

swAuthBackendNonNakResponsesFromSupplica.name: swAuthBackendNonNakResponsesFromSupplicant
swAuthBackendNonNakResponsesFromSupplica.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine receives a response from the Supplicant to an initial EAP-Request, and the response is something other than EAP-NAK (i.e., rxResp becomes TRUE, causing the state machine to transition from REQUEST to RESPONSE, and the response is not an EAP-NAK). Indicates that the Supplicant can respond to the Authenticator's chosen EAP-method.

swAuthBackendAuthSuccesses.name: swAuthBackendAuthSuccesses
swAuthBackendAuthSuccesses.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine receives an EAP-Success message from the Authentication Server (i.e., a Success becomes TRUE, causing a transition from RESPONSE to SUCCESS). Indicates that the Supplicant has successfully authenticated to the Authentication Server.

swAuthBackendAuthFails.name: swAuthBackendAuthFails
swAuthBackendAuthFails.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine receives an EAP-Failure message from the Authentication Server (i.e., a Fail becomes TRUE, causing a transition from RESPONSE to FAIL). Indicates that the Supplicant has not authenticated to the Authentication Server.

swMacAuthSessionStatsTable.name: swMacAuthSessionStatsTable
swMacAuthSessionStatsTable.description: A table that contains the session statistics objects for the Authenticator PAE associated with each MAC address. An entry appears in this table for each MAC address that may authenticate access to itself.

swMacAuthSessionStatsEntry.name: swMacAuthSessionStatsEntry
swMacAuthSessionStatsEntry.description: The session statistics information for an Authenticator PAE. This shows the current values being collected for each session that is still in progress, or the final values for the last valid session on each MAC address where there is no session currently active.

swAuthSessionOctetsRx.name: swAuthSessionOctetsRx
swAuthSessionOctetsRx.description: The number of octets received in user data frames from this MAC address during the session.

swAuthSessionOctetsTx.name: swAuthSessionOctetsTx
swAuthSessionOctetsTx.description: The number of octets transmitted in user data frames to this MAC address during the session.

swAuthSessionFramesRx.name: swAuthSessionFramesRx
swAuthSessionFramesRx.description: The number of user data frames received from this MAC address during the session.

swAuthSessionFramesTx.name: swAuthSessionFramesTx
swAuthSessionFramesTx.description: The number of user data frames transmitted to this MAC address during the session.

swAuthSessionId.name: swAuthSessionId
swAuthSessionId.description: A unique identifier for the session, in the form of a printable ASCII string of at least three characters.

swAuthSessionAuthenticMethod.name: swAuthSessionAuthenticMethod
swAuthSessionAuthenticMethod.description: The authentication method used to establish the session.

swAuthSessionTime.name: swAuthSessionTime
swAuthSessionTime.description: The duration of the session in units of hundredth of a second.

swAuthSessionTerminateCause.name: swAuthSessionTerminateCause
swAuthSessionTerminateCause.description: The reason for the session termination.

swAuthSessionUserName.name: swAuthSessionUserName
swAuthSessionUserName.description: The User-Name representing the identity of the Supplicant PAE.

swDot1xAuthMACAddress.description: The MAC address associated with this host.

swDot1xAuthenticatorPAEState.description: The current value of the Authenticator PAE state machine.

swDot1xAuthBackendAuthState.description: The current state of the Backend Authentication state machine.

swDot1xAuthAuthControlledStatus.name: swDot1xAuthAuthControlledStatus
swDot1xAuthAuthControlledStatus.description: The authenticate state of the host.

swDot1xAuthAssignVID.description: The VID assigned by the RADIUS server.

swDot1xAuthAssignPriority.description: The priority assigned by the RADIUS server.

swDot1xAuthEapolFramesRx.description: The number of valid EAPOL frames of any type that have been received by this Authenticator.

swDot1xAuthEapolReqFramesTx.name: swDot1xAuthEapolReqFramesTx
swDot1xAuthEapolReqFramesTx.description: The number of EAP Request frames (other than Rq/Id frames) that have been transmitted by this Authenticator.

swDot1xAuthInvalidEapolFramesRx.name: swDot1xAuthInvalidEapolFramesRx
swDot1xAuthInvalidEapolFramesRx.description: The number of EAPOL frames that have been received by this Authenticator for which the frame type is not recognized.

swDot1xAuthBackendResponses.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine sends an initial Access-Request packet to the Authentication server (i.e., executes sendRespToServer on entry to the RESPONSE state). swDot1xAuthBackendNonNakResponsesFromSup.name: swDot1xAuthBackendNonNakResponsesFromSupplicant
swDot1xAuthBackendNonNakResponsesFromSup.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine receives a response from the Supplicant to an initial EAP-Request, and the response is something other than EAP-NAK (i.e., rxResp becomes TRUE, causing the state machine to transition from REQUEST to RESPONSE, and the response is not an EAP-NAK). Indicates that the Supplicant can respond to the Authenticator's chosen EAP-method.

swDot1xAuthBackendAuthSuccesses.name: swDot1xAuthBackendAuthSuccesses
swDot1xAuthBackendAuthSuccesses.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine receives an EAP-Success message from the Authentication Server (i.e., a Success becomes TRUE, causing a transition from RESPONSE to SUCCESS). Indicates that the Supplicant has successfully authenticated to the Authentication Server.

swDot1xAuthBackendAuthFails.name: swDot1xAuthBackendAuthFails
swDot1xAuthBackendAuthFails.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine receives an EAP-Failure message from the Authentication Server (i.e., a Fail becomes TRUE, causing a transition from RESPONSE to FAIL). Indicates that the Supplicant has not authenticated to the Authentication Server.

swDot1xAuthSessionStatsTable.name: swDot1xAuthSessionStatsTable
swDot1xAuthSessionStatsTable.description: A table that contains the session statistics objects for the Authenticator PAE associated with each host. An entry appears in this table for each host that may authenticate access to itself.

swDot1xAuthSessionStatsEntry.name: swDot1xAuthSessionStatsEntry
swDot1xAuthSessionStatsEntry.description: The session statistics information for an Authenticator PAE. This shows the current values being collected for each session that is still in progress, or the final values for the last valid session on each host where there is no session currently active.

swDot1xAuthSessionOctetsRx.name: swDot1xAuthSessionOctetsRx
swDot1xAuthSessionOctetsRx.description: The number of octets received in user data frames from this host during the session.

swDot1xAuthSessionOctetsTx.name: swDot1xAuthSessionOctetsTx
swDot1xAuthSessionOctetsTx.description: The number of octets transmitted in user data frames to this host during the session.

swDot1xAuthSessionFramesRx.name: swDot1xAuthSessionFramesRx
swDot1xAuthSessionFramesRx.description: The number of user data frames received from this host during the session.

swDot1xAuthSessionFramesTx.name: swDot1xAuthSessionFramesTx
swDot1xAuthSessionFramesTx.description: The number of user data frames transmitted to this host during the session.

swDot1xAuthSessionId.name: swDot1xAuthSessionId
swDot1xAuthSessionId.description: A unique identifier for the session, in the form of a printable ASCII string of at least three characters.

swDot1xAuthSessionAuthenticMethod.name: swDot1xAuthSessionAuthenticMethod
swDot1xAuthSessionAuthenticMethod.description: The authentication method used to establish the session.

swDot1xAuthSessionTime.name: swDot1xAuthSessionTime
swDot1xAuthSessionTime.description: The duration of the session in units of hundredth of a second.

swDot1xAuthSessionTerminateCause.name: swDot1xAuthSessionTerminateCause
swDot1xAuthSessionTerminateCause.description: The reason for the session termination.

swDot1xAuthSessionUserName.name: swDot1xAuthSessionUserName
swDot1xAuthSessionUserName.description: The User-Name representing the identity of the Supplicant PAE.

swRadiusForceDownPortNumber.name: swRadiusForceDownPortNumber
swRadiusForceDownPortNumber.description: The port number on which the RADIUS server is forced to terminate the network service.

swRadiusForceDownMacAddr.name: swRadiusForceDownMacAddr
swRadiusForceDownMacAddr.description: The user's MAC address on which the RADIUS server is forced to terminate the network service.

swAuthenticatedPortCtrlTable.name: swAuthenticatedPortCtrlTable
swAuthenticatedPortCtrlTable.description: A table used to configure the port's 802.1x capability.

swAuthenticatedPortCtrlEntry.name: swAuthenticatedPortCtrlEntry
swAuthenticatedPortCtrlEntry.description: The Port number and authenticator control for a Port.

swAuthenticatedPortNumber.name: swAuthenticatedPortNumber
swAuthenticatedPortNumber.description: The Authenticated Port number associated with this Port.

swAuthenticatedPortCapabilities.name: swAuthenticatedPortCapabilities
swAuthenticatedPortCapabilities.description: Indicates the PAE functionality that this Port supports and that it may be managed through this MIB.

swMacBasedPaePortTable.name: swMacBasedPaePortTable
swMacBasedPaePortTable.description: A table of system level information for each port supported by the MAC-based Port Access Entity. An entry appears in this table for each port of this system.

swMacBasedPaePortEntry.name: swMacBasedPaePortEntry
swMacBasedPaePortEntry.description: The port number, protocol version and initialization control for a Port by MAC based mode.

swMacBasedPaePortNumber.name: swMacBasedPaePortNumber
swMacBasedPaePortNumber.description: The port number associated with this Port.

swMacBasedPaeMacAddress.name: swMacBasedPaeMacAddress
swMacBasedPaeMacAddress.description: Specifies the MAC address used to initialize the 802.1X authentication state machine of some or all ports or used to reauthenticate the device connected to the port.

swMacBasedPaePortInitializeOrReauthStatu.name: swMacBasedPaePortInitializeOrReauthStatus
swMacBasedPaePortInitializeOrReauthStatu.description: This is used to execute MAC-Based Port initialization or reauthentication, so it is necessary to set swMacBasedPaeMacAddress before this action can be initialized. Choosing 'initialize' causes the port to be initialized in MAC-based mode. Choosing 'reauthenticate' causes the port to be reauthenticated in MAC-based mode. The attribute value reverts to 'other' once the initialization or reauthentication has been done.

swMacBasedPaeTable.name: swMacBasedPaeTable
swMacBasedPaeTable.description: A table used to reauthenticate or initialize a host.

swMacBasedPaeEntry.name: swMacBasedPaeEntry
swMacBasedPaeEntry.description: The port number, MAC address and initialization or reauthentication control for a host by MAC based mode.

swMacBasedPaePort.name: swMacBasedPaePort
swMacBasedPaePort.description: The port number associated with this Port.

swMacBasedPaeMac.name: swMacBasedPaeMac
swMacBasedPaeMac.description: Specifies the MAC address used to initialize the 802.1X authentication state machine of the host or used to reauthenticate the host on the port.

swMacBasedPaeInitOrReauthStatus.name: swMacBasedPaeInitOrReauthStatus
swMacBasedPaeInitOrReauthStatus.description: This is used to execute MAC-based Port initialization or reauthentication. Choosing 'initialize' causes the host to be initialized in MAC-based mode. Choosing 'reauthenticate' causes the host to be reauthenticated in MAC-based mode. The attribute value reverts to 'other' once the initialization or reauthentication has been done.

swPaeAuthSysFwdPdu.name: swPaeAuthSysFwdPdu
swPaeAuthSysFwdPdu.description: This object indicates the global setting to control the forwarding of the EAPOL PDU.

swPaeAuthSysMaxUser.name: swPaeAuthSysMaxUser
swPaeAuthSysMaxUser.description: This object indicates the global limitation on the maximum number of users that can be learned via 802.1X authentication. The maximum entry range is (0..N), the value N means the maximum number. It is determined by the project itself. Value 0 means no-limit.

swPaeAuthConfigTable.name: swPaeAuthConfigTable
swPaeAuthConfigTable.description: A table that contains the configuration objects for the Authenticator PAE associated with each port. An entry appears in this table for each port that may authenticate access to itself.

swAuthStateTable.name: swAuthStateTable
swAuthStateTable.description: A table that contains the status objects for the Authenticator PAE associated with each host. An entry appears in this table for each host that may authenticate access to itself.

swAuthStateEntry.name: swAuthStateEntry
swAuthStateEntry.description: The information for an Authenticator PAE.

swAuthPortNumber.name: swAuthPortNumber
swAuthPortNumber.description: The PAE Port number associated with this Port.

swAuthMacAddress.name: swAuthMacAddress
swAuthMacAddress.description: The address associated with this MAC address.

swAuthAuthControlledStatus.name: swAuthAuthControlledStatus
swAuthAuthControlledStatus.description: The authenticate state of the host.

swAuthAssignVid.name: swAuthAssignVid
swAuthAssignVid.description: The VID assigned by the RADIUS server.

swAuthAssignPriority.name: swAuthAssignPriority
swAuthAssignPriority.description: The priority assigned by the RADIUS server.

swAuthenticatorPAEState.name: swAuthenticatorPAEState
swAuthenticatorPAEState.description: The current value of the Authenticator PAE state machine.

swAuthBKdAuthState.name: swAuthBKdAuthState
swAuthBKdAuthState.description: The current state of the Backend Authentication state machine.

swPaeAuthConfigEntry.name: swPaeAuthConfigEntry
swPaeAuthConfigEntry.description: The configuration information for an Authenticator PAE.

swPaeAuthFwdPdu.name: swPaeAuthFwdPdu
swPaeAuthFwdPdu.description: This object indicates the per port setting to control the forwarding of EAPOL PDU.

swPaeAuthMaxUser.name: swPaeAuthMaxUser
swPaeAuthMaxUser.description: This object indicates the limitation on the maximum number of users by port. The max entry range is (0..N), the value N means the max number. It is determined by project itself. Value 0 means no-limit.

swCompoundAuthPortTable.name: swCompoundAuthPortTable
swCompoundAuthPortTable.description: A table that contains compound authentication information for each port.

swCompoundAuthPortEntry.name: swCompoundAuthPortEntry
swCompoundAuthPortEntry.description: The compound authentication configuration information for a port.

swCompoundAuthPortIndex.name: swCompoundAuthPortIndex
swCompoundAuthPortIndex.description: The compound authentication port number associated with this port.

swCompoundAuthPortAuthMode.name: swCompoundAuthPortAuthMode
swCompoundAuthPortAuthMode.description: This object sets the authorization mode. Port-based: If one of the attached hosts passes the authentication, all the hosts on the same port will be granted access to the network. If the user fails the authorization, this port will keep trying the next authentication. Host-based: Every user can be authenticated individually. The client can start authentication on specific authentication VLAN(s).

swCompoundAuthPortMethod.name: swCompoundAuthPortMethod
swCompoundAuthPortMethod.description: This object sets the method for compound authentication settings. None: The system level setting of individual authentication still takes effect. Thus suppose that the compound authentication method of a port is set to any but MAC-AC is disabled, JWAC and 802.1x enabled, then the user must pass either the JWAC or 802.1x method. The following is the relation of the compound authentication method and the configuration of the individual authentication method. (1) If compound authentication methods is not set to none: The port's authentication method will depend on the compound authentication method. An individual authentication method's setting is ignored. (2) If compound authentication methods is set to none: This port is in single-auth mode. The port's authentication method will depend on the individual authentication method's setting. Any: If any one of the authentication methods (802.1x, MAC-AC, WAC and JWAC) passes, then pass. dot1xImpb: Dot1x will be verified first, and then IMPB will be verified. Both authentication methods need to be passed to make the authentication successful. impbJwac: IMPB will be verified first, and then JWAC will be verified. Both authentication methods need to be passed to make the authentication successful. impbWac: IMPB will be verified first, and then WAC will be verified. Both authentication methods need to be passed to make the authentication successful. macImpb: MAC-AC will be verified first, and then IMPB will be verified. Both authentication methods need to be passed to make the authentication successful. macJwac: MAC-AC will be verified first. If client passed MAC authentication, JWAC will be verified. Both authentication methods need to be passed to make the authentication successful.

swCompoundAuthPortAuthVLANs.name: swCompoundAuthPortAuthVLANs
swCompoundAuthPortAuthVLANs.description: This object sets the Authentication VLAN(s). If the authentication VLAN is not specified, It means to not care which VLAN the client comes from, the client will be authenticated if the client's MAC (not care the VLAN) is not authenticated. After the client is authenticated, the client will not be reauthenticated when received from other VLANs. When the port's authorization mode is changed to port based, previously authentication VLAN(s) on this port will be cleared. Note: For the compound VLAN specification, the value should be separated by ',' or '-'. Such as: 1,4,7 or 1,4,7-9 .

swGuestVlanTable.name: swGuestVlanTable
swGuestVlanTable.description: A table containing configuration information for guest VLANs configured into the device by local or network management. All entries are permanent and will be restored after the device reset.

swGuestVlanEntry.name: swGuestVlanEntry
swGuestVlanEntry.description: Information for a guest VLAN configured into the device by local or network management.

swGuestVlanId.name: swGuestVlanId
swGuestVlanId.description: The VLAN ID referring to this guest VLAN.

swGuestVlanPorts.name: swGuestVlanPorts
swGuestVlanPorts.description: The set of ports which are permanently assigned to the guest VLAN member for this guest VLAN by management. Note: For on-going projects which need to support old-style commands as well, the rules for guest VLAN setting are: (1) Compound authentication mode is not none: You need to specify the guest VLAN by this command or individual authentication method's guest VLAN setting will be ignored. (2) Compound authentication mode is none: This port is in single authentication mode. Individual authentications use their guest VLAN settings configured by their individual guest VLAN commands. The setting of config guest_vlan will be ignored

swGuestVlanRowStatus.name: swGuestVlanRowStatus
swGuestVlanRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swAuthorizationAttributes.name: swAuthorizationAttributes
swAuthorizationAttributes.description: This object indicates the authorization status. When the authorization for attributes is enabled, whether the authorized attributes (for example VLAN, 802.1p default priority, and ACL) assigned by the RADIUS server or local database will be accepted or not will depend on the individual module setting.

swAuthServerFailoverState.name: swAuthServerFailoverState
swAuthServerFailoverState.description: This object indicates the authentication server failover state. block: Block the client. local: Use the local DB to authenticate the client. permit: The client is always regarded as authenticated.

swAuthMACFormatCase.name: swAuthMACFormatCase
swAuthMACFormatCase.description: This object indicates the case format of the authentication MAC address for RADIUS authentication. uppercase: Using uppercase format, the formatted is: AA-BB-CC-DD-EE-FF. lowercase: Using lowercase format, the formatted is: aa-bb-cc-dd-ee-ff.

swAuthMACFormatDelimiter.name: swAuthMACFormatDelimiter
swAuthMACFormatDelimiter.description: This object indicates the delimiter format of authentication MAC address for RADIUS authentication. none: Not using any delimiter, the format is: AABBCCDDEEFF hyphen: Using '-' as delimiter, the format is: AA-BB-CC-DD-EE-FF colon: Using ':' as delimiter, the format is: AA:BB:CC:DD:EE:FF dot: Using '.' as delimiter, the format is: AA.BB.CC.DD.EE.FF

swAuthMACFormatDelimiterNumber.name: swAuthMACFormatDelimiterNumber
swAuthMACFormatDelimiterNumber.description: This object indicates the delimiter number of authentication MAC address for RADIUS authentication. delimiter-number-1: single delimiter, the format is: AABBCC.DDEEFF delimiter-number-2: double delimiter, the format is: AABB.CCDD.EEFF delimiter-number-5: multiple delimiter, the format is: AA.BB.CC.DD.EE.FF Note: while swAuthMACFormatDelimiter is none(1), the delimiter number will not take effect.
